      comments: "Decent from Marisa Tomei"
    }
    actor {
      name: "Kevin Bacon"
      comments: "Decent from Kevin Bacon"
    }
    cast: "Decent from the rest of the cast"
    comments: "Decent to Pretty Good Acting"
  }
  story {
    writer {
      name: "Dan Fogelman"
    }
    comments: "Pretty Bad to Decent Story (Entertaining story overall as it is a retelling of the makeover story similar Pretty Woman and She\'s All That, but it does share a lot of the same cliches as well has many of the same faults that Rom-Coms of the time period have (making the movie incredibly predictable); The story does fall apart in the final 30-40 minutes as it becomes incredibly predictable and borderline cringy)"
  }
  screenplay {
    writer {
      name: "Dan Fogelman"
    }
    comments: "Decent Screenplay (Pretty Funny/light-hearted Rom-Com overall with safe dialogue, symbolism is pretty shallow as it follows the same message as many of the Rom-Coms of the era; the foreshadowing was more cliche than anything (which made the movie incredibly predictable))"
  }
  score {
    composer {
      name: "Christophe Beck"
    }
    composer {
      name: "Nick Urata"
    }
    comments: "Decent Score"
  }
  cinematography {
    cinematographer {
      name: "Andrew Dunn"
    }
    comments: "Bad Cinematography (I\'m not sure if it was just the way I was viewing it but the filter they were using made the movie feel incredibly blurry as it gave this movie a dream-like feel)"
  }
  sound: "Decent Sound"
  editing {
    editor {
      name: "Lee Haxall"
    }
    comments: "Decent Editing"
  }
  plot_structure: "Plot Structure was pretty boilerplate for a Rom-Com but the final arc (last 30-49) becomes very cliche as it tries to show the \'meaning\' of the movie"
  pacing: "Pacing was decent for the most part but is incredibly rushed in the final 30-40 minutes of the movie (which is kinda sad considering this was where the message of the movie was supposed to be brought out); Runtime was fine (maybe an extra 10 minutes could\'ve helped with the ending)"
  climax: "Climax was not executed well as it was very cringy and was incredibly formulaic for a Rom-Com"
  tone: "Tone was very similar to other Rom-Coms of the era"
  final_notes: ""
  overall: "Overall, a decent watch that has some memorable moments from the interactions between Ryan Gosling and Steve Carell, but overall is a pretty formulaic Rom-Com that does not have a strong ending considering how predictable the movie gets"
}
